00159 ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
00160 /// Error and Status flags of the joint. 
00161 /// Bit 0: Overcurrent flag. This flag is set if overcurrent limit is exceeded. \n
00162 /// Bit 1: Undervoltage flag. This flag is set if supply voltage to low for motor operation. \n
00163 /// Bit 2: Overvoltage flag. This flag is set if the motor becomes switched off due to overvoltage. \n
00164 /// Bit 3: Overtemperature flag. This flag is set if overtemperature limit is exceeded. \n
00165 /// Bit 4: Motor halted flag. This flag is set if motor has been switched off. \n
00166 /// Bit 5: Hall error flag. This flag is set upon a hall error. \n
00167 /// Bit 6: Encoder error flag. This flag is set upon an encoder error. \n
00168 /// Bit 7: Winding error flag. [currently not used] \n
00169 /// Bit 8: Cycle time violation. [currently not used] \n
00170 /// Bit 9: Initialization error of sine commutation. This flag is set if initialization is failed. \n
00171 /// Bit 10: Position mode flag. This flag is set when the module is in positioning mode. \n
00172 /// Bit 11: Position end flag. This flag becomes set if the motor has been stopped at the end position. \n
00173 ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
00174 class ErrorAndStatus : public YouBotJointParameterReadOnly {
00175 friend class YouBotJoint;
00176   public:
00177     ErrorAndStatus();
00178 
00179     virtual ~ErrorAndStatus();
00180 
00181     void getParameter(unsigned int& parameter) const;
00182 
00183     void toString(std::string& value);
00184 
00185 
00186   private:
00187     void getYouBotMailboxMsg(YouBotSlaveMailboxMsg& message, TMCLCommandNumber msgType, const YouBotJointStorage& storage) const;
00188 
00189     void setYouBotMailboxMsg(const YouBotSlaveMailboxMsg& message, const YouBotJointStorage& storage);
00190 
00191     std::string getName() const {return this->name;};
00192 
00193     ParameterType getType() const {return this->parameterType;};
00194

00196 
00197     unsigned int value;

00203 };
